My=20
favorite=20
theme in=20
modern finance is:
=09Interest rates were very low for a very long time.=09Now they are higher=
.=09People just forgot that that was a possibility, and were surprised.

There are various important manifestations of this =E2=80=94=C2=A0a frozen =
US housing market, the 2023 regional banking crisis =E2=80=94=C2=A0but it i=
s pervasive in strange small ways too. For instance, for a long time, the w=
ay that debt investing worked was=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B that you bough=
t some bonds, and their prices went up or down, and you had inflows or outf=
lows, so you had various reasons to sell the bonds you had or buy new bonds=
. If you asked =E2=80=9Cwhat drives demand for bonds,=E2=80=9D you=E2=80=99=
d get answers about client inflows or relative value or whatever. But in 20=
24 you get=20
stories like this:

