if the stock actually drops to zero? As a matter of sensible trading, you w=
ill probably at least consider covering some of your short immediately. But=
 if you do that, people will get mad: =E2=80=9CYou didn=E2=80=99t really be=
lieve the stock was going to zero,=E2=80=9D they will say; =E2=80=9Cyou jus=
t wanted to create a quick panic so you could profit.=E2=80=9D


  [3] Obviously there are exceptions. David Einhorn is a pretty famous shor=
t seller who is *mostly* a long investor. Bill Ackman is mostly a value inv=
estor who has had some famous activist shorts. But the more modern trend do=
es seem to be toward specialization, at least in activist (as opposed to qu=
iet) short selling.


  [4] There are ways to finesse this =E2=80=94 the standard argument is tha=
t clients should allocate some money to your short fund to allow them to in=
crease their allocation to long investments =E2=80=94 but it=E2=80=99s a mo=
re complicated pitch than =E2=80=9Cmy fund usually goes up.=E2=80=9D=20


  [5] Also, if you do one big short report a month, you might not want to r=
isk a huge portion of your capital on that report being right: A portfolio =
consisting solely of your activist short ideas will not be very diversified=
. Selling the idea to someone with more capital and more, different ideas m=
akes the bet more sensible.


  [6] For instance: =E2=80=9CSEBI did not allege any aspect of our descript=
ion [of a particular incident] was false. Rather, it argued that CESTAT loo=
ked at the earlier case and alleged that we =E2=80=98sensationalized or dis=
torted certain facts=E2=80=99 by using the word =E2=80=98scandal=E2=80=99 t=
o describe the prior alleged INR 6.8 billion scheme by Adani that resulted =
in a 239-page order from the Commissioner of Customs detailing evidence of =
fraud, an INR 250 million (U.S. $4.6 million) fine, and extensive subsequen=
t legal proceedings.=E2=80=9D=20


  [7] It also hints that it might be illegal even for Hindenburg to trade o=
n the report itself, though that is less clear.


