<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The basic business model of an activist short =
seller is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Investigate a company, ideally using =
only public sources.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
ckground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Find out that the company is bad.=
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Short its stock.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Put out a public report describing your findings =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cthis company is bad=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0in a zi=
ppy, emphatic, hopefully accurate way.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5=
px;">Watch the stock go down, because people read your report, realize that=
 the company is bad=C2=A0and dump the stock.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bot=
tom: 5px;">Profit, by covering your short at the new, lower market price re=
flecting the new, accurate, bad information that you have published about t=
he company.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-c=
olor: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>
</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously some short sellers, sometimes, will =
deviate from this ideal model. They will investigate a company using nonpub=
lic information, for instance, or their report will be inaccurate. But assu=
ming that they follow the ideal model: Is this okay? Are you allowed to do =
this?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the US, I think the answer is clearly yes, =
but people do get mad about it. There is some apparent intuition that it is=
 market manipulation: You are betting that a stock will fall, and then you =
are=C2=A0<em>making=C2=A0</em>it fall (by publishing your report), and that=
 seems somehow like cheating. In practice, most people who don=E2=80=99t li=
ke it will complain that the report is inaccurate =E2=80=94=C2=A0it is more=
 clearly market manipulation if the report is wrong =E2=80=94=C2=A0but I th=
ink that some of this really is driven by suspicion of the whole business m=
odel. Even if the report is entirely accurate and based on public informati=
on, something about the model strikes people as icky.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is a slight complication of that business=
 model:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Investigate a company, ideally using =
only public sources.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Find out that=
 the company is bad.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Write a repor=
t=C2=A0describing your findings =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cthis company is bad=
=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0in a zippy, emphatic, hopefully accurate way.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">
<em>Sell=C2=A0</em>that report to some other, larger, better capitalized he=
dge fund.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">
<em>That=C2=A0</em>fund shorts the stock.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom=
: 5px;">You publish the report.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Wa=
tch the stock go down, because people read your report, realize that the co=
mpany is bad=C2=A0and dump the stock.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5p=
x;">The other hedge fund profits, by covering its short at the new, lower m=
arket price reflecting the new, accurate, bad information that you have pub=
lished about the company.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It=
 gives you a cut of the profits.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is a more complicated model, but it makes=
 more sense given the economic and social reality of activist short selling=
:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you are an activist short seller, y=
ou are normally pretty specialized: Finding and investigating bad companies=
 is your calling, and you=E2=80=99re not also out there making tons of deep=
-value long bets or whatever.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-=
3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !impor=
tant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Stocks mostly go up, so it is har=
d to run a hedge fund that only makes short bets: Who would want to invest?=
<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: trans=
parent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Also it is=C2=A0<em>just possible=
=C2=A0</em>that the personal characteristics that make=C2=A0you a good acti=
vist short seller (cynicism, combativeness) will also make you bad at raisi=
ng money from clients.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">So if you=
=E2=80=99re good at identifying bad companies and writing punchy reports ab=
out how they=E2=80=99re bad, you might not be in a position to make a big b=
et on your report, because you just don=E2=80=99t have a lot of capital.<a =
class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpar=
ent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Meanwhile plenty of other, bigger=
 hedge funds would love to have some good short ideas, but don=E2=80=99t wa=
nt to pay a full-time analyst to go around digging for frauds. They=E2=80=
=99ll happily give you a share of the winnings if you bring them your ideas=
.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What about this model? I think people find it =
even ickier. In particular, there is something about the=C2=A0<em>collusion=
=C2=A0</em>between the short researcher and the hedge fund that rubs people=
 the wrong way. Surely it is unfair for the hedge fund to trade on the rese=
archer=E2=80=99s report before it is published. The report is nonpublic inf=
ormation (it hasn=E2=80=99t been published yet), and it is material (if it =
causes the stock to go down), so isn=E2=80=99t it insider trading for the h=
edge fund to trade on it?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, I think that the answer in US law is no=
, this is fine. Insider trading, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/35934584.195413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9u=
L2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMzAvc2hhZG93LXRyYWRpbmctaXMtYmFkLXNvbWV0aW1lcz9jbXB=
pZD1CQkQwNzAyMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2=
xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA3MDImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cB2d9616d0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">
I like to say</a>, is not about fairness; it=E2=80=99s about theft. It=E2=
=80=99s illegal to trade on material nonpublic information that you get in =
violation of some duty to someone; trading on <em>your own=C2=A0</em>inform=
ation =E2=80=94=C2=A0like =E2=80=9CI am about to publish this report=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0is fine. Here, the short researcher owns the information=
 (the report), and=C2=A0<em>wants=C2=A0</em>the hedge fund to trade, so it=
=E2=80=99s fine. But I should stress:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Nothing here is legal advice.</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It icks people out, even if it is legal, =
and there are constant rumors of <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/35934584.195413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6=
aW5lL2FyY2hpdmUvMjAyMy8wMy93YWxsLXN0cmVldC1tdWRkeS13YXRlcnMtYWN0aXZpc3Qtc2h=
vcnQtc2VsbGVycy10ZXNsYS1nYW1lc3RvcC82NzI3NzQv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0cf6=
8cd4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;">US investigations into collusion among short sellers</a>.</li=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The US has somewhat unusual insider t=
rading rules, and in other countries there is more of a risk that=C2=A0<em>=
any=C2=A0</em>trading on material nonpublic information might be illegal.</=
li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Last year, US activist short research firm Hin=
denburg Research <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
5934584.195413/aHR0cHM6Ly9oaW5kZW5idXJncmVzZWFyY2guY29tL2FkYW5pLw/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cB7b3e86a2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;">published a report</a> on India=E2=80=99s=
 Adani Group, titled =E2=80=9CAdani Group: How The World=E2=80=99s 3rd Rich=
est Man Is Pulling The Largest Con In Corporate History.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9C=
Over two weeks, the report <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/35934584.195413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbG=
VzLzIwMjMtMDItMDkvaGluZGVuYnVyZy1yZXNlYXJjaC1hZGFuaS1wYXBlci1ib29zdHMtbmF0a=
GFuLWFuZGVyc29uLXMtbmFtZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNzAyMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVt=
PWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA3MDImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWd=
uPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB18f7aaf5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">
wiped out more than $110 billion</a> from the conglomerate=E2=80=99s pre-Hi=
ndenburg value, pushed some of its bonds to distressed levels and caused Ad=
ani to shelve stock and bond offerings.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yesterday, Hindenburg published an =E2=80=9C<a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35934584.195413/aHR0=
cHM6Ly9oaW5kZW5idXJncmVzZWFyY2guY29tL2FkYW5pLXVwZGF0ZS1zZWJpLw/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBa37b8dfb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;">Adani Update =E2=80=93 Our Response To India=
=E2=80=99s Securities Regulator SEBI</a>.=E2=80=9D At=C2=A0Bloomberg News, =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35934584.195413/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDctMDIvaGluZGVuY=
nVyZy1sYXNoZXMtb3V0LW9uLWluZGlhLXJlZ3VsYXRvci1vdmVyLWFkYW5pLXJlcG9ydD9jbXBp=
ZD1CQkQwNzAyMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2x=
ldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA3MDImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB9ca1c76c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">Sanjay P R reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The firm also posted on its website the full =
=E2=80=9Cshow cause=E2=80=9D notice it said it received from the Securities=
 and Exchange Board of India, or Sebi, in June, which states that Hindenbur=
g=E2=80=99s report on the Adani Group had certain misrepresentations and in=
accurate statements that were meant to mislead readers.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the 46-page document, Sebi said Hindenburg =
=E2=80=9Chas resorted to extrapolation and conjecture to emphasize some fac=
ts and understate others in favor of negative inference against Adani Group=
 Companies.=E2=80=9D It also said the short seller cited a broker banned fr=
om the securities market, shaking investors=E2=80=99 trust in the regulator=
y framework.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hindenburg in turn said India=E2=80=99s market=
s regulator failed to address the fraud allegations in its report last year=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sebi =E2=80=9Cseems more interested in pursuin=
g those who expose such practices=E2=80=9D while its investigation into bil=
lionaire Adani=E2=80=99s empire has hit a wall, Hindenburg said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/35934584.195413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2xpZGVzaGFyZS5uZXQvc2Vj=
cmV0LzZ2VVEyMFFNb0pQSURh/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB39e50fae" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the Seb=
i notice</a> that Hindenburg posted. There is, of course, some argument ove=
r whether Hindenburg=E2=80=99s Adani report was accurate. Sebi says:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">During investigation, it was also observed tha=
t the Hindenburg Report contained certain misrepresentations/ inaccurate st=
atements. These misrepresentations built a convenient narrative through sel=
ective disclosures, reckless statements and catchy headlines, in order to m=
islead readers of the report and cause panic in Adani Group stocks, thereby=
 deflating prices to the maximum extent possible and profit from the same. =
=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It was observed that the Hindenburg Report del=
iberately sensationalized and distorted certain facts through the use of ca=
tchy=C2=A0<em>headlines=C2=A0</em>such as =E2=80=9CScandal.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hindenburg argues, though, that Sebi doesn=E2=
=80=99t really identify any material inaccuracies; it just doesn=E2=80=99t =
like that the Hindenburg report is written in the zippy, argumentative styl=
e of a short report.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-6" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
ckground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But Hindenburg also points out that=C2=A0the d=
iscussion of alleged inaccuracies is brief and starts on page 24 of the 46-=
page Sebi order. Sebi=E2=80=99s main point is something else: Hindenburg mo=
netized the trade by selling it to a bigger hedge fund, and Sebi doesn=E2=
=80=99t like that. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/35934584.195413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMj=
QtMDctMDIvaGluZGVuYnVyZy1sYXNoZXMtb3V0LW9uLWluZGlhLXJlZ3VsYXRvci1vdmVyLWFkY=
W5pLXJlcG9ydD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNzAyMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0=
bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA3MDImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R=
1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC9ca1c76c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">
Bloomberg reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sebi=E2=80=99s notice also named US hedge fund=
 Kingdon Capital Management as an involved party, stating that Kingdon knew=
 about Hindenburg=E2=80=99s research on the Adani Group before it was publi=
shed and had a profit-sharing pact with the short-seller on its trades.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hindenburg shared a draft of the Adani report =
with Kingdon in November 2022, nearly two months before it published the re=
port, according to the Sebi show cause notice. In return Kingdon agreed to =
share 30% of its net profits from trading securities related to Adani with =
Hindenburg. That profit-sharing then got reduced to 25%, due to the cost of=
 setting up these trades. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As of June 1, the Kingdon fund returned $4.1 m=
illion of the gains from the Adani short sale to Hindenburg while another $=
1.4 million has yet to be shared, according to Sebi.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, this is the fairly standard business mo=
del =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cmuch of the notice seemed designed to imply tha=
t our legal and disclosed investment stance was something secret or insidio=
us,=E2=80=9D says Hindenburg =E2=80=94=C2=A0but you don=E2=80=99t have to l=
ike it. Sebi says:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Noticee No. 1 (Hindenburg) colluded with Notic=
ee No. 3 (Mr. Mark E. Kingdon) along with Noticees Nos. 4, 5 and 6 i.e.=C2=
=A0<em>Kingdon entities</em>, in a scheme devised to use advance knowledge =
of non-public information (=E2=80=9C<em>NPI</em>=E2=80=9D) regarding the ex=
istence, timing, and overall nature of the Report, to enable Noticee No. 6 =
to build short positions in the futures of AEL [Adani Enterprises Ltd.] and=
 share profits accrued from squaring-off the positions at prices deflated d=
ue to publication of the Hindenburg Report in a manner designed to lower sc=
rip prices to the maximum extent possible. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Therefore, it is alleged that Hindenburg and K=
ingdon entities dealt only in securities of AEL while in possession of NPI =
regarding existence, timing, and overall nature of the Hindenburg Report on=
 Adani Group securities including the securities of AEL and profited unlawf=
ully from the price deflated due to publication of the Report, without ensu=
ring compliance with the [Research Analyst] regulations. This also constitu=
ted an unfair trade practice which prejudiced good faith dealings in the sh=
ares of AEL, by ordinary investors.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That at least suggests that, even if every wor=
d in the Hindenburg report was=C2=A0<em>true</em>, it would still be <em>il=
legal</em>, because Hindenburg showed it to Kingdon, and Kingdon traded on =
it, before it was published.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-7=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !import=
ant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a> People really do not like activist short sellers and think they should=
 be illegal, and some of those people are securities regulators.</p>
