</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">People just forgot that that was =
a possibility, and were surprised.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are various important manifestations of =
this =E2=80=94=C2=A0a frozen US housing market, the 2023 regional banking c=
risis =E2=80=94=C2=A0but it is pervasive in strange small ways too. For ins=
tance, for a long time, the way that debt investing worked was=E2=80=8B=E2=
=80=8B=E2=80=8B that you bought some bonds, and their prices went up or dow=
n, and you had inflows or outflows, so you had various reasons to sell the =
bonds you had or buy new bonds. If you asked =E2=80=9Cwhat drives demand fo=
r bonds,=E2=80=9D you=E2=80=99d get answers about client inflows or relativ=
e value or whatever. But in 2024 you get <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/35934584.195413/aHR0cHM6Ly9uZXdzLmJsb29tYmVyZ2xhdy5j=
b20vY2FwaXRhbC1tYXJrZXRzL2NvcnBvcmF0ZS1hbWVyaWNhcy1pbnRlcmVzdC1wYXltZW50cy1=
